public class TreeCellFX<T,​C extends CellController<T>> extends javafx.scene.control.TreeCell<T> implements IndexedCellFXable<T,​C>

Implementation of TreeCell that manages the display of its contents using a CellController.

    • treeItemFXBinding

      public javafx.beans.binding.ObjectBinding<TreeItemFX<T>> treeItemFXBinding()

      Returns an ObjectBinding that reflects the parent Item Property cast to TreeItemFX.

      Binding Passthrough Definition: (TreeItemFX) Cell.getItem()

      Details

      1. Convenience binding that eliminates the need to cast the TreeItem content of this TreeCellFX by storing its value as a pre-casted TreeItemFX.
      2. If the content of this TreeCellFX is not an instance of TreeItemFX, a ClassCastException is thrown.
      Returns:
      An ObjectBinding that reflects the parent Item Property cast to TreeItemFX.

    • contentVisibleBinding

      public javafx.beans.binding.BooleanBinding contentVisibleBinding()

      A BooleanBinding that reflects whether the current content of this TreeCellFX is currently visible or not.

      Details

      1. If the content of this TreeCellFX is null, the BooleanBinding returned by this method will reflect false.
      2. The BooleanBinding returned by this method is bound to a RecursiveBinding, therefore, the binding will reflect accurate results, even when the content of this TreeCellFX changes or is null.
      3. The BooleanBinding returned by this method is defined in the TreeCellFX constructor.
      Returns:
      A BooleanBinding that reflects whether the current content of this TreeCellFX is currently visible or not.
